'''Bogomila Welsh-Ovcharov''' (born 1940, [[Sofia]])<ref>[http://dap.library.uu.nl/frames.html?zoeken Digitaal Album Promotorum] at Utrecht University.</ref> is an [[art historian]] at the [[University of Toronto at Mississauga]] and authority on the art of [[Vincent van Gogh]].<ref>{{cite web|author=James Adams |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/art-and-architecture/vincent-van-gogh-the-lost-arles-sketchbook/article32836911/ |title=Van Gogh's long-lost sketches draw a clearer picture of his wild years in Provence |publisher=The Globe and Mail |date=2017-01-05 |accessdate=2017-06-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.greatpast.utoronto.ca/GreatMinds/ShowBannerUTM.asp?ID=95 |title=University of Toronto - Great Past - Great Minds Bio |publisher=Greatpast.utoronto.ca |accessdate=2017-06-09}}</ref> Her book ''Van Gogh: The Lost Arles Sketchbook'', contains reproductions of sketches said to be by the artist, but the authenticity of which has been disputed.<ref>{{cite web|author=Barbara Casassus |url=http://www.thebookseller.com/news/controversry-france-over-vincent-van-gogh-book-441206 |title=Controversy in France over Vincent van Gogh book |publisher=The Bookseller |date=2016-12-05 |accessdate=2017-06-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Murray Whyte |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/visualarts/2016/11/20/reputations-are-on-the-line-in-van-gogh-battle.html |title=Reputations are on the line in van Gogh battle &#124; Toronto Star |publisher=Thestar.com |date=2016-11-20 |accessdate=2017-06-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Mark Brown, Arts correspondent |url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2016/nov/15/newly-discovered-van-gogh-drawings-labelled-imitations-museum |title=Newly discovered 'Van Gogh' drawings labelled imitations by museum &#124; Art and design |publisher=The Guardian |date=2016-11-15 |accessdate=2017-06-09}}</ref>

