{{for|his birthplace|Constantin Daicoviciu, Caraş-Severin}} {{Infobox person | image = Constantin Daicoviciu.jpg | image_size = 200px | name = Constantin Daicoviciu | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1898|3|1|mf=y}} | birth_place = [[Constantin Daicoviciu, Caraş-Severin|Căvăran]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|1973|5|27|1898|3|11|mf=y}} | death_place = Cluj | other_names = | known_for = | occupation = [[historian]], [[Archaeology|archaeologist]] }}
'''Constantin Daicoviciu''' ({{IPA-ro|konstanˈtin ˈdajkovit͡ʃju}}; March 1, 1898, [[Constantin Daicoviciu, Caraş-Severin|Căvăran]] – May 27, 1973, Cluj-Napoca) was a [[Romania]]n [[historian]] and [[Archaeology|archaeologist]].
He was [[Rector (academia)|rector]] (president) of [[Babeş-Bolyai University]] of [[Cluj]], and a [[list of members of the Romanian Academy|member of the Romanian Academy]].
His son, [[Hadrian Daicoviciu]] (1932–1984) was also a historian.
Since his death in 1973, the commune in the [[Banat]] where he was born in bears his name.
