{{Expand Spanish|Francisco L. Urquizo|date=February 2011}} {{unreferenced|date=September 2013}} {{Infobox military person |name=Francisco L. Urquizo |birth_date= {{birth date|1891|6|21}} |death_date= {{death date|1969|4|6}} (aged 77) |image=Urquizo.jpg |image_size=250 |caption=General Francisco L. Urquizo Benavides |nickname= |birth_place=[[San Pedro de las Colonias]], [[Coahuila]] |death_place=[[Mexico City]] |placeofburial= |placeofburial_label= |allegiance=Mexico (antireeleccionista revolutionary forces) |branch=[[Liberation Army of the South]] 1911, Federal Army 1912-1913, [[Constitutional Army]] 1913-1920, [[Mexican Army]] 1920, 1936-1969 |rank=[[File:Gral divn.gif|30px]] [[General officer|General]] |serviceyears=1911-1920, 1936-1969 |commands=[[Secretariat of National Defense (Mexico)|Secretariat of National Defence]] |battles=[[Mexican Revolution]]: *Attack on San Pedro de las Colonias *[[Ten Tragic Days]] *Battle of Candela *Battle of Torreon *Taking of Monterrey *Fights of Apizaco, Rinconada and Aljibes *Tlaxcalantongo |awards= {{plainlist| *[[Belisario Domínguez Medal of Honour]] *[[Military decorations of Mexico#Legion of Honor|Mexican Legion of Honour]] }} }}
'''Francisco Luis Urquizo Benavides''' (21 June 1891, [[San Pedro de las Colonias]], [[Coahuila]] – 6 April 1969, [[Mexico City]]) was a Mexican soldier, revolutionary general, writer and historian. With [[Mariano Azuela]], [[Mauricio Magdaleno]], [[Martín Luis Guzmán]] and [[José Vasconcelos]], he was one of the main authors of the so-called ''novela revolucionaria'', which was a literary account of episodes in the [[Mexican Revolution]]. He was twice [[Secretariat of National Defense|Secretary of National Defense]].
==Principal Published Works== *''Memorias de campaña'' *''Tropa Vieja'' *''¡Viva Madero!'' *''Páginas de la Revolución'' *''La ciudadela quedó atrás'' *''Fui soldado de levita de esos de caballería'' *''México - Tlaxcalantongo'' *''Morelos, genio militar de la Independencia'' *''Europa Central en 1922'' *''A un Joven Militar Mexicano'' *''Madrid de los Años Veinte'' *''Recuerdo Que...'' *''Tres de Diana'' *''Charlas de Sobremesa'' *''El Capitán Arnaud'' *''Lo Incognoscible''
