'''Ross Cowan''' is a Scottish historian and author specialising in [[Roman military history]].
== Education and career ==
Cowan was born in [[Glasgow]].{{Citation needed|date=June 2018}} He studied at the [[University of Glasgow]], completing an MA in classical civilisation in 1997 and a PhD in history in 2003.<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=https://independent.academia.edu/RossCowan|title=Ross Cowan - Academia.edu|website=independent.academia.edu}}</ref> His doctoral thesis was on the [[Praetorian Guard]] and [[Legio II Parthica]], entitled ''Aspects of the Severan Field Army AD 193–238''.<ref name="ospreypublishing.com">{{cite web|url=https://ospreypublishing.com/ross-cowan|title=Ross Cowan|website=ospreypublishing.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.paperplus.co.nz/author/ross-cowan-247796|title=Ross Cowan - Books|website=www.paperplus.co.nz}}</ref> He was been a fellow of the [[Society of Antiquaries of Scotland|Society of the Antiquaries of Scotland]] since 1999.<ref name="ospreypublishing.com"/>
Since earning his PhD Cowan has been an [[independent scholar]], writing several books on Roman military history for [[Osprey Publishing]].<ref name=":0" /> He currently resides in [[Renfrewshire, Scotland]].{{Citation needed|date=June 2018}}
